testsuite.name: com.limac.diffservice.service.DiffServiceImplSpec

testcase.name: non existing diffId should be saved in the repository
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: null, rightInput: existingRightInput] accordingly with the input type LEFT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: newLeftInput, rightInput: existingRightInput] accordingly with the input type LEFT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: null, rightInput: existingRightInput] accordingly with the input type LEFT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: newLeftInput, rightInput: existingRightInput] accordingly with the input type LEFT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: null, rightInput: null] accordingly with the input type LEFT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: newLeftInput, rightInput: null] accordingly with the input type LEFT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: existingLeftInput, rightInput: newRightInput] accordingly with the input type RIGHT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: existingLeftInput, rightInput: null] accordingly with the input type RIGHT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: null, rightInput: newRightInput] accordingly with the input type RIGHT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: null, rightInput: null] accordingly with the input type RIGHT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: existingLeftInput, rightInput: newRightInput] accordingly with the input type RIGHT
if the diffId already exists the Diff updated should be [leftInput: existingLeftInput, rightInput: null] accordingly with the input type RIGHT
findById should return the Diff if the diffId is found
findById should throw NotFoundException if the diffId does not exists
diff should be able define the result EQUAL
diff should be able define the result DIFFERENT_SIZE
diff should be able define the result SAME_SIZE_BUT_DIFFERENT
diff should compare the left and right inputs and return the diff results
diff should throw MissingInputException if any input is missing
